{"word":"κρύπτω","slug":"κρύπτω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κρύπτω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hide, cover, cloak</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, attic:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>κάρα κρυψάμενος</el> <i>having cloaked his</i> head, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to hide oneself, lie hidden</i>, of setting stars, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to cover in the earth, bury</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to hide, conceal, keep secret</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>κεκρυμμένος</el> <i>secret</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to conceal</i> something from one, <el>μή με κρύψηις τοῦτο</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>ἑαυτόν</el>) <i>to hide oneself, lie hidden</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}